cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence modeling and machine translation. It may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it focuses on speech translation. Additionally, it may be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel attention mechanism. It could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with natural language processing and translation. Finally, it may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the processing of information from a lattice structure.
